British Automobile ManufacturersAssociation expects exports to the United States to more thandouble in 1987 to 56,595 units from 26,200 in 1986, associationpresident G.W. Whitehead told reporters at the New York AutoShow.    "We feel this is the appropriate occasion to announce thereturn of British cars as an important force in the U.S.imported car market," said Whitehead, who is also president ofJaguar Plc's U.S. unit.    Whitehead said increased sales will result from intensifiedNorth American marketing by British automakers. Reuter&#3;